  "prompt": "What was the hardest video game ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"hardest\" video game ever is subjective and often depends on personal preferences, gaming experiences, and skill levels. However, several titles are frequently mentioned in the context of extreme difficulty:\n\n1. **Dark Souls Series** - Known for its punishing combat mechanics, intricate enemy designs, and unforgiving boss battles, the Dark Souls games challenge players to learn from their mistakes and master the gameplay.\n\n2. **Super Meat Boy** - This platformer features fast-paced levels filled with deadly obstacles and requires precise timing, making it a tough but rewarding experience.\n\n3. **Battletoads** - Particularly famous for its challenging gameplay, especially the speeder bike level, Battletoads has become emblematic of frustration in gaming.\n\n4. **Ninja Gaiden (2004)** - Renowned for its difficult bosses and fast-paced combat, this game is often cited as one of the more challenging action titles.\n\n5. **Celeste** - While it offers an emotional narrative, the platforming challenges can be quite difficult, especially for players aiming to complete it with full collectibles.\n\n6. **The Binding of Isaac** - This roguelike offers a steep learning curve and challenging gameplay, especially at higher difficulty levels.\n\nThese games are just a few examples and may not resonate with everyone. Difficulty levels can also vary depending on individual play styles and strategies. Ultimately, the hardest game is often the one that challenges a player the most personally.",
